{
  "stem": "11964.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This was-- to us, it was just unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So we stayed a few days, through this shiva, and then we returned home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "When we returned back to Radomsko, we found out that our house had been totally bombed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "There was just rubble.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We couldn't find anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I remember we looked-- went to the side, when we found pieces of dishes, and the string of the piano, and such things.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Pieces of wallpaper.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And here we were, my mother, my father, and the three of us, who have lived in great comfort, without a home, without a pillow, without a blanket, without anything to our names except those few personal suitcases.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, somebody took pity on us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was a young man-- he recently married-- who knew us very, very well and invited us to share his apartment.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was a railroad apartment, and he gave us one room.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember coming to that apartment, and they very graciously said, this will be your room.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we realized that we will have to share a bedroom with my mother and father, all five of us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And share the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was a traumatic experience to my parents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Very traumatic experience.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was a Jewish family, obviously.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was 1939.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the beginning of the war, and we were already homeless.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were without any means of income.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had-- we were totally left without any means for sustenance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was the question, how in the world are we going to live?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the Germans took care of that, because soon after, they created a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you couldn't exist in the ghetto unless you registered in order to get ration cards.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
